OL,3,CFirst case of livestock virus
OL,4,CBluetongue identified in Wales
OL,6,FThe first cases of the Bluetongue (BTV
OL,7,F-3) virus have been detected in Wales
OL,8,Fthis year, just a week after
OL,9,Frestrictions were eased.
OL,11,FThe virus was discovered in cattle at
OL,12,Ftwo premises - one in Presteigne,
OL,13,FPowys and another in Chepstow,
OL,14,FMonmouthshire.
OL,16,FThe discovery follows the easing of
OL,17,Frestrictions over the summer which
OL,18,Fprevented the movement of livestock to
OL,19,FWales from a restricted zone without a
OL,20,Fnegative test.
