OL,3,CFirst case of livestock virus
OL,4,CBluetongue identified in Wales
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government eased
OL,7,Frestrictions as temperatures were
OL,8,Fexpected to be low enough to "reduce
OL,9,Fvirus transmission by midges."
OL,11,FBluetongue is primarily transmitted by
OL,12,Fmidges as well as by infected male
OL,13,Fanimals during breeding.
OL,15,FA Welsh Government spokesperson said:
OL,16,F"We urge livestock keepers to continue
OL,17,Fto be vigilant and follow stringent
OL,18,Fbiosecurity measures - including to
OL,19,Fpractice safe sourcing of livestock.
